"title": "1348: covenant, God's with Abraham",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1348",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God's gracious promise made to Abraham, and repeated to his descendants, to bless both them and, through them, the whole world. In response God calls for faithful obedience, expressed particularly in the outward sign of circumcision.</p>\n<h2>Features of the Abrahamic covenant</h2>\n<h3>The covenant is based upon God's gracious promise</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:18\">GAL 3:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:4-Gen15:7\">GEN 15:4–15:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:4-Gen17:8\">GEN 17:4–17:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:10\">GEN 18:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:14\">GEN 18:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:13-Heb6:15\">HEB 6:13–6:15</a></p>\n<h3>The covenant was confirmed by sacrifice</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:9-Gen15:18\">GEN 15:9–15:18</a></p>\n<h3>The covenant was given in perpetuity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:7\">GEN 17:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:13\">GEN 17:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:19\">GEN 17:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:15-1Chr16:17\">1CH 16:15–16:17</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:8-Ps105:10\">PSA 105:8–105:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:23-Jer33:25\">JER 33:23–33:25</a></p>\n<h2>God's promises to Abraham</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:2-Gen12:3\">GEN 12:2–12:3</a></strong></p>\n<h3>God promised the land of Canaan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:8\">GEN 17:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:7\">GEN 12:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:18-Gen15:21\">GEN 15:18–15:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:4\">EXO 6:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:3\">JOS 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:8\">NEH 9:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:5\">ACT 7:5</a></p>\n<h3>God promised that Abraham would be the father of a nation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:5\">GEN 15:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:2\">GEN 12:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:4-Gen17:6\">GEN 17:4–17:6</a> <em>The change of name from Abram to Abraham is a sign of God's covenant with him</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:16\">GEN 17:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:17\">GEN 22:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:11-Heb11:12\">HEB 11:11–11:12</a></p>\n<h3>God promised a relationship with himself</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:8\">GEN 17:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:24\">GEN 26:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:13\">DEU 29:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:32\">MAT 22:32</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:26\">MRK 12:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:6\">EXO 3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:32\">ACT 7:32</a></p>\n<h2>The requirements of the covenant</h2>\n<h3>Obedience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:9-Gen17:14\">GEN 17:9–17:14</a></strong> <em>Circumcision is the sign of Abraham's commitment to God's covenant with him</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:18\">GEN 22:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:5\">GEN 26:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:11\">NUM 32:11</a> <em>by contrast, the consequences of disobedience</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:8\">HEB 11:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:17-Heb11:19\">HEB 11:17–11:19</a></p>\n<h3>Faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:6\">GEN 15:6</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:8\">NEH 9:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:3\">ROM 4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:11-Rom4:12\">ROM 4:11–4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:18\">ROM 4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:6-Gal3:7\">GAL 3:6–3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:8-Heb11:12\">HEB 11:8–11:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:23\">JAS 2:23</a></p>\n<h2>God's faithfulness to the covenant</h2>\n<h3>God remembers his promise</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:42\">PSA 105:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:2\">GEN 21:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:24\">GEN 50:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:1\">EXO 33:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:17\">ACT 7:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:15\">HEB 6:15</a></p>\n<h3>God shows compassion for his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:23\">2KI 13:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:24-Exod2:25\">EXO 2:24–2:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:13-Exod32:14\">EXO 32:13–32:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:27\">DEU 9:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:72-Luke1:73\">LUK 1:72–1:73</a></p>\n<h2>The scope of the covenant</h2>\n<h3>The covenant continued through Isaac, not Ishmael</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:19-Gen17:21\">GEN 17:19–17:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:12\">GEN 21:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:7-Rom9:8\">ROM 9:7–9:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:28\">GAL 4:28</a></p>\n<h3>The covenant confirmed through Abraham, Isaac and Jacob</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:42\">LEV 26:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:24\">GEN 26:24</a> <em>Isaac</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:13-Gen28:14\">GEN 28:13–28:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:12\">GEN 32:12</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:6\">EXO 3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:8\">DEU 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:8\">ACT 7:8</a></p>\n<h3>The people of Israel are heirs to the covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:12-Deut29:13\">DEU 29:12–29:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:25\">ACT 3:25</a></p>\n<h3>All nations will be blessed through Abraham</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:18\">GEN 18:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:4\">GEN 26:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:25\">ACT 3:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:8-Gal3:9\">GAL 3:8–3:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:14\">GAL 3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:29\">GAL 3:29</a></p>",
